Amid Russian and Ukraine’s war crisis, actor Yul Edochie has reminded Nigerians of their seemingly ‘sad’ reality. In a recent tweet, the 2023 presidential aspirant expressed empathy over the ongoing war between Russia and Ukraine. He however used the opportunity to jog the memory of the masses concerning the state of insecurity, hike in the price of foodstuff and surge in ritual killings in the country;   What damages most taxi engines in Nigeria – Erigga     Lateef Adedimeji as Tinubu in movie: I’m prepared for…     Why I feel like giving up, by Mr Macaroni   He tweeted: “As we worry about Ukraine, we must not lose sight of the situation in our own country. “The hardship is unbearable. People are being killed every day like flies either by robbers or bandits. “Food prices are skyrocketing. For 100 naira someone can take your life just to feed himself.”